                    <persName xml:lang="en" xml:id="name1616-6" source="#bib1616-5">Mar Asia</persName>
                    <idno type="URI">http://syriaca.org/person/1616</idno>
                    <idno type="URI">http://www.csc.org.il/db/browse.aspx?db=SB&amp;sL=M&amp;sK=Mar%20Asia&amp;sT=keywords</idno>
                    <note xml:lang="en" type="abstract" xml:id="abstract1616-1">Mar Asia converted to the life of an
          itinerant monk. He travels to <placeName ref="http://syriaca.org/place/104">Jerusalem</placeName> and <placeName ref="http://syriaca.org/place/563">Sinai</placeName> and visited monasteries. He became a monk himself and used hnana (oil
          mixed with dust of sacred sites) to heal others.</note>
